{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":16020,"record_hash":"sha256:b83b645792f7370e9c83e6414e82788eeceafeb8c7a74e0fe7f2c8d20a120ca6","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:35:33.658Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 67c9a2\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 3164\nOutput:\n# First POC Implementation Contract\n\nThis is the implementation contract for the first Agent Session Capture POC.\nWhen this page conflicts with broader architecture or future-work notes, this\npage wins for the first implementation.\n\n## Goal\n\nBuild the smallest safe proof that GitButler can capture agent log metadata from\nan explicit Codex or Claude transcript path and write redacted session data into\nGitMeta.\n\nThe first patch should prove:\n\n- GitButler CLI can invoke capture behind a hidden feature-gated command.\n- A new crate can parse Codex and Claude JSONL transcripts from an explicit path.\n- Capture writes shareable-ready GitButler session data under `gitbutler:*`.\n- Transcript envelopes are always captured, redacted, and deduplicated.\n- Repeated capture is idempotent.\n\n## Implement Only This\n\n- New crate: `crates/but-agentlog` (`but_agentlog` in Rust code).\n- Hidden CLI command behind feature flag `agentlog`:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog capture \\\n  --agent codex \\\n  --transcript-path <path> \\\n  [--target project]\n```\n\n- `codex` and `claude` are the supported agents in the first implementation.\n- Keep agent handling closed and explicit. Codex and Claude should force a small\n  shared parser/output boundary, not a plugin framework.\n- `--transcript-path` is required.\n- Default target is `project`.\n- GitMeta writes use shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys.\n- The command does not serialize, push, fetch, or sync GitMeta.\n\n## Do Not Implement Yet\n\n- No Cursor support.\n- No background watcher.\n- No session discovery.\n- No `CODEX_THREAD_ID` lookup.\n- No recent-file heuristics.\n- No branch inference.\n- No commit inference from `HEAD`.\n- No GitMeta push/fetch/sync/serialization.\n- No UI surface.\n- No dependency on `but-api`, `but-db`, `but-ctx`, `but-claude`, `but-cursor`,\n  or legacy virtual branch APIs.\n- No branch/PR/commit association keys.\n\n## Dependency Decision\n\nUse the GitMeta GitHub repository pinned to an ex\n[TRUNCATED]\n     |\n| [REDACTED:entropy] | Not implemented in first POC                                            |\n\nAll stored agentlog values copied from transcripts are redacted before writing.\nThe POC does not store raw provider session ids.\n\n## Future Associations\n\nDo not implement branch, PR, change, or commit associations in this POC. Later,\nwhen GitButler has an explicit target, write relationship references like:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nThe durable session remains project-scoped. See\n[Future Use Cases](future-use-cases.md).\n\n## Acceptance Tests\n\nMinimum tests before calling the POC done:\n\n- `cargo test -p but-agentlog` passes.\n- Parses Codex and Claude fixture JSONL from explicit paths.\n- Missing transcript path fails clearly.\n- Unsupported agent fails clearly.\n- Default capture writes `gitbutler:agent-sessions` and\n  `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`.\n- No `meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:*` keys are written for main session\n  data.\n- Source metadata uses basename-only `source-name`.\n- Transcript envelopes contain only the slim per-record fields.\n- Envelope `source_key` joins to source metadata.\n- Running capture twice on the same fixture captures `N` then `0` new metadata\n  records and appends transcript envelopes only once.\n- Growing the fixture captures only new records.\n- Missing transcript list backfills from stored envelopes and record hashes.\n- Malformed final non-empty line is tolerated as partial write.\n- Malformed middle line fails.\n- Session ids are converted to hashed safe session keys.\n- Human and JSON output do not contain the full transcript path.\n\n## Done Means\n\nThe first POC is done when:\n\n- The command exists but is hidden and feature-gated.\n- The new crate has focused unit/integration tests.\n- GitButler builds with the feature enabled.\n- Capture can be run against a fixture or real Codex/Claude transcript.\n- Repeated capture is idempotent.\n- No future-work behavior accidentally lands in the first patch.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:35:33.658Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}